17namespace webrtc {

19template <typename T>
20bool AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::Config::IsOk() const {
21 if (max_bit_rate < 32000 && max_bit_rate != -1)
22 return false;
23 if (max_payload_size_bytes < 120 && max_payload_size_bytes != -1)
24 return false;
25
26 switch (sample_rate_hz) {
27 case 16000:
28 if (max_bit_rate > 53400)
29 return false;
30 if (max_payload_size_bytes > 400)
31 return false;
32 return (frame_size_ms == 30 || frame_size_ms == 60) &&
33 (bit_rate == 0 || (bit_rate >= 10000 && bit_rate <= 32000));
34 case 32000:
35 if (max_bit_rate > 160000)
36 return false;
37 if (max_payload_size_bytes > 600)
38 return false;
39 return T::has_swb &&
40 (frame_size_ms == 30 &&
41 (bit_rate == 0 || (bit_rate >= 10000 && bit_rate <= 56000)));
42 default:
43 return false;
44 }
45}
46
47template <typename T>
48AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::AudioEncoderIsacT(const Config& config) {
49 RecreateEncoderInstance(config);
50}
51
52template <typename T>
53AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::~AudioEncoderIsacT() {
54 RTC_CHECK_EQ(0, T::Free(isac_state_));
55}
56
57template <typename T>
58int AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::SampleRateHz() const {
59 return T::EncSampRate(isac_state_);
60}
61
62template <typename T>
63size_t AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::NumChannels() const {
64 return 1;
65}
66
67template <typename T>
68size_t AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::Num10MsFramesInNextPacket() const {
69 const int samples_in_next_packet = T::GetNewFrameLen(isac_state_);
70 return static_cast<size_t>(rtc::CheckedDivExact(
71 samples_in_next_packet, rtc::CheckedDivExact(SampleRateHz(), 100)));
72}
73
74template <typename T>
75size_t AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::Max10MsFramesInAPacket() const {
76 return 6; // iSAC puts at most 60 ms in a packet.
77}
78
79template <typename T>
80int AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::GetTargetBitrate() const {
81 return config_.bit_rate == 0 ? kDefaultBitRate : config_.bit_rate;
82}
83
84template <typename T>
85void AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::SetTargetBitrate(int target_bps) {
86 // Set target bitrate directly without subtracting per-packet overhead,
87 // because that's what AudioEncoderOpus does.
88 SetTargetBitrate(target_bps,
89 /*subtract_per_packet_overhead=*/false);
90}
91
92template <typename T>
93void AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::OnReceivedTargetAudioBitrate(int target_bps) {
94 // Set target bitrate directly without subtracting per-packet overhead,
95 // because that's what AudioEncoderOpus does.
96 SetTargetBitrate(target_bps,
97 /*subtract_per_packet_overhead=*/false);
98}
99
100template <typename T>
101void AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::OnReceivedUplinkBandwidth(
102 int target_audio_bitrate_bps,
103 absl::optional<int64_t> /*bwe_period_ms*/) {
104 // Set target bitrate, subtracting the per-packet overhead if
105 // WebRTC-SendSideBwe-WithOverhead is enabled, because that's what
106 // AudioEncoderOpus does.
107 SetTargetBitrate(
108 target_audio_bitrate_bps,
109 /*subtract_per_packet_overhead=*/send_side_bwe_with_overhead_);
110}
111
112template <typename T>
113void AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::OnReceivedUplinkAllocation(
114 BitrateAllocationUpdate update) {
115 // Set target bitrate, subtracting the per-packet overhead if
116 // WebRTC-SendSideBwe-WithOverhead is enabled, because that's what
117 // AudioEncoderOpus does.
118 SetTargetBitrate(
119 update.target_bitrate.bps<int>(),
120 /*subtract_per_packet_overhead=*/send_side_bwe_with_overhead_);
121}
122
123template <typename T>
124void AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::OnReceivedOverhead(
125 size_t overhead_bytes_per_packet) {
126 overhead_per_packet_ = DataSize::Bytes(overhead_bytes_per_packet);
127}
128
129template <typename T>
130AudioEncoder::EncodedInfo AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::EncodeImpl(
131 uint32_t rtp_timestamp,
132 rtc::ArrayView<const int16_t> audio,
133 rtc::Buffer* encoded) {
134 if (!packet_in_progress_) {
135 // Starting a new packet; remember the timestamp for later.
136 packet_in_progress_ = true;
137 packet_timestamp_ = rtp_timestamp;
138 }
139 size_t encoded_bytes = encoded->AppendData(
140 kSufficientEncodeBufferSizeBytes, [&](rtc::ArrayView<uint8_t> encoded) {
141 int r = T::Encode(isac_state_, audio.data(), encoded.data());
142
143 if (T::GetErrorCode(isac_state_) == 6450) {
144 // Isac is not able to effectively compress all types of signals. This
145 // is a limitation of the codec that cannot be easily fixed.
146 r = 0;
147 }
148 RTC_CHECK_GE(r, 0) << "Encode failed (error code "
149 << T::GetErrorCode(isac_state_) << ")";
150
151 return static_cast<size_t>(r);
152 });
153
154 if (encoded_bytes == 0)
155 return EncodedInfo();
156
157 // Got enough input to produce a packet. Return the saved timestamp from
158 // the first chunk of input that went into the packet.
159 packet_in_progress_ = false;
160 EncodedInfo info;
161 info.encoded_bytes = encoded_bytes;
162 info.encoded_timestamp = packet_timestamp_;
163 info.payload_type = config_.payload_type;
164 info.encoder_type = CodecType::kIsac;
165 return info;
166}

168template <typename T>
169void AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::Reset() {
170 RecreateEncoderInstance(config_);
171}
172
173template <typename T>
174absl::optional<std::pair<TimeDelta, TimeDelta>>
175AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::GetFrameLengthRange() const {
176 return {{TimeDelta::Millis(config_.frame_size_ms),
177 TimeDelta::Millis(config_.frame_size_ms)}};
178}
179
180template <typename T>
181void AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::SetTargetBitrate(int target_bps,
182 bool subtract_per_packet_overhead) {
183 if (subtract_per_packet_overhead) {
184 const DataRate overhead_rate =
185 overhead_per_packet_ / TimeDelta::Millis(config_.frame_size_ms);
186 target_bps -= overhead_rate.bps();
187 }
188 target_bps = rtc::SafeClamp(target_bps, kMinBitrateBps,
189 MaxBitrateBps(config_.sample_rate_hz));
190 int result = T::Control(isac_state_, target_bps, config_.frame_size_ms);
191 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(result, 0);
192 config_.bit_rate = target_bps;
193}
194
195template <typename T>
196void AudioEncoderIsacT<T>::RecreateEncoderInstance(const Config& config) {
197 RTC_CHECK(config.IsOk());
198 packet_in_progress_ = false;
199 if (isac_state_)
200 RTC_CHECK_EQ(0, T::Free(isac_state_));
201 RTC_CHECK_EQ(0, T::Create(&isac_state_));
202 RTC_CHECK_EQ(0, T::EncoderInit(isac_state_, /*coding_mode=*/1));
203 RTC_CHECK_EQ(0, T::SetEncSampRate(isac_state_, config.sample_rate_hz));
204 const int bit_rate = config.bit_rate == 0 ? kDefaultBitRate : config.bit_rate;
205 RTC_CHECK_EQ(0, T::Control(isac_state_, bit_rate, config.frame_size_ms));
206
207 if (config.max_payload_size_bytes != -1)
208 RTC_CHECK_EQ(
209 0, T::SetMaxPayloadSize(isac_state_, config.max_payload_size_bytes));
210 if (config.max_bit_rate != -1)
211 RTC_CHECK_EQ(0, T::SetMaxRate(isac_state_, config.max_bit_rate));
212
213 // Set the decoder sample rate even though we just use the encoder. This
214 // doesn't appear to be necessary to produce a valid encoding, but without it
215 // we get an encoding that isn't bit-for-bit identical with what a combined
216 // encoder+decoder object produces.
217 RTC_CHECK_EQ(0, T::SetDecSampRate(isac_state_, config.sample_rate_hz));
218
219 config_ = config;
220}
